description: Thrown when the RMN (Risk Management Network) has cursed the destination chain.
Thrown when the router has not set the original sender address.
Thrown when the caller is not the configured router address.
Thrown when the destination chain selector does not match the configured one.
Thrown when an invalid extra arguments tag is used.
Thrown when the message size exceeds the maximum allowed size.
Thrown when the gas limit exceeds the maximum per-message gas limit.
Thrown when attempting to send a token with amount zero.
Thrown when the onRamp has reached its maximum fee storage capacity.
Thrown when too many tokens are involved in the transfer.
Thrown when attempting to send an unsupported token.
Thrown when enforceOutOfOrder is true but allowOutOfOrderExecution is false.
Thrown when the source token data exceeds the configured maximum size.
